Gov. Bev Perdue,

Regarding the Appropriation Act of 2009, I am dismayed to hear that the NC State Legislature is considering repealing the tuition grant that has been promised to the current students (class of 2009 and 2010) of The North Carolina School of Science and Mathematics. 

NCSSM is an exemplary school that has filled a void in the public school system for almost 30 years.  Many of the students that attend have exhausted all of the math courses at their home schools by tenth grade.  These are precocious students with bright futures ahead of them.  They would have been one of the top students at their home high schools and qualified for several scholarships.  Instead, they chose the road of leaving their family and friends behind to pursue excellence in education.   The challenge at NCSSM is great even for the brightest students and they work very hard late into the night five or six nights per week to complete the homework load.

